Tip cloud-repo-create-wall
  When runtime=cloud
  Say You cannot create a NEW GitHub repo from this session, and no token in this VM will fix it. Two walls stack: the built-in GitHub tools authenticate as the Claude GitHub App (App tokens cannot create user-owned repos), and the agent proxy enforces an authorized repository set, refusing GitHub API calls outside it even with your own valid PAT. Pre-creating the repo in the UI does not help either, since pushing to it is blocked the same way. What DOES work: a user-authenticated GitHub MCP connector (its traffic routes through Anthropic, never through this proxy), creating the repo from a local session, or delegating to a GitHub Actions workflow. Deploying is unaffected: the Vercel MCP ships a file tree directly and needs no repo at all.
